Researchers have found that this plant-eater, although covered with armor and resembling a walking tank, was probably threatened by meat-eating dinosaurs.
The heavily armored dinosaur used a red and white disguise to hide from predators, and used a shielding technique known as counter-shadowing, which is also used by many modern animals.
