In the middle of the room at the Fridman Gallery in New York, you can see many faces - white, black and brown, almost imperceptibly identical - hanging on cables from the ceiling.
The 30 portraits were created by artist Heather Dewey-Hagborg from cheeks and haircuts sent to her by Chelsea Manning.
